FBIS4-16281 "drsov073_r_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 Azerbaijan Azeri Forces Rebuff Offensive Azeri Forces Rebuff Offensive LD1404181594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1631 GMT 14 Apr 94 LD1404181594 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By AZERTAC correspondent Alla Baula for TASS] [Text] Baku April 14 TASS -- Armenian troops launched a fresh offensive in the Geranboi-Terter section of the Azerbaijani-Armenian front on Thursday, the Azerbaijani Defence Ministry said. It said Azerbaijani forces rebuffed the attack. The Armenians had to retreat after their attempt to seize the village of Gyullidzha in the Agdam district of Azerbaijan failed. They lost two tanks and several people were killed. Azerbaijani troops also destroyed Armenian positions which were used to shell Azerbaijani villages in the district, the report said. The ministry said that Armenian forces continue shelling border villages in the Kazakh district of Azerbaijan and the border outpost Kilid in the Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic.
